Module 3: Input Validation & Output Encoding
1. Syntax vs. Semantic Validation
Syntax Validation: Checks if the data looks correct (e.g., Is this string a validly formatted email address structure?).

Semantic Validation: Checks if the data makes sense in context (e.g., Is this email domain actually real? Does this email already belong to an active account in our database?).

2. Form Security: Vulnerable vs. Secure Implementation
The Vulnerable Form Handler (XSS and Processing Flaws)

<?php
// INSECURE: Directly trusting user inputs
$username = $_POST['username'];
$email = $_POST['email'];
$age = $_POST['age'];

// No structural validation, no sanitization
echo "<h3>Welcome, " . $username . "!</h3>"; 
echo "<p>Your registered email is: " . $email . "</p>";
Why this fails: If an attacker passes <script>alert('XSS')</script> as the username, it executes directly in the user's browser. If they pass a string like "abc" to age, your database logic may break.

The Fixed Form Handler (Secure filter_var and htmlspecialchars)

<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

$errors = [];
$clean = [];

if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'POST') {
    
    // 1. Syntax Validation via filter_var()
    $raw_email = $_POST['email'] ?? '';
    $validated_email = filter_var($raw_email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL);
    
    if ($validated_email === false) {
        $errors[] = "Please enter a structurally valid email address.";
    } else {
        $clean['email'] = $validated_email;
    }

    // 2. Syntax Validation for Integers (Age)
    $raw_age = $_POST['age'] ?? '';
    $options = ["options" => ["min_range" => 18, "max_range" => 120]];
    $validated_age = filter_var($raw_age, FILTER_VALIDATE_INT, $options);

    if ($validated_age === false) {
        $errors[] = "You must be between 18 and 120 years old to register.";
    } else {
        $clean['age'] = $validated_age;
    }

    // 3. String Sanitization & Semantic Check
    $raw_username = trim($_POST['username'] ?? '');
    if (preg_match('/^[a-zA-Z0-9_]{3,20}$/', $raw_username) !== 1) {
        $errors[] = "Username must be alphanumeric and between 3-20 characters.";
    } else {
        $clean['username'] = $raw_username;
    }

    // Processing if no errors found
    if (empty($errors)) {
        // [Semantic Validation step occurs here: Check database if email/username exists]
        // Proceed with user registration logic safely...
    }
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head><title>Secure Registration</title></head>
<body>

    <?php if (!empty($errors)): ?>
        <ul style="color: red;">
            <?php foreach ($errors as $error): ?>
                <li><?= htmlspecialchars($error, ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8'); ?></li>
            <?php endforeach; ?>
        </ul>
    <?php endif; ?>

    <?php if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'POST' && empty($errors)): ?>
        <h3>Welcome, <?= htmlspecialchars($clean['username'], ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8'); ?>!</h3>
        <p>Your registered email is: <?= htmlspecialchars($clean['email'], ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8'); ?></p>
    <?php endif; ?>

</body>
</html>


